node.title: Live - 'No more T-shirts pulled up': Mask rules tightened, Govt to reveal next two phases of Omicron response
node.description: Here's what you need to know.
node.content: ["Twenty-nine people have now tested positive for the highly infectious Omicron variant in the community, 10 of whom were confirmed as cases on Tuesday.\u00a0", "The variant of COVID-19, which produces less severe illness but is incredibly transmissible, found a foothold in the community over the weekend when nine people tested positive for the virus in Motueka. The family had travelled to Auckland the weekend prior for a wedding and other social events.", "The January Omicron Cluster, which currently spans Auckland, Palmerston North and Nelson-Tasman - with two cases now also under investigation in Tauranga - is projected to increase to possibly tens of thousands of cases, with experts warning the strain could infect half of the population in a matter of months.", "Health officials are now calling on eligible New Zealanders to urgently get their booster shots - the third dose has been found to provide an extra layer of protection against the variant.\u00a0", "Follow Newshub's live updates below - app users, click here", "7:20am - Kia ora, good morning, and welcome to Newshub's live coverage of the COVID-19 Omicron outbreak for Wednesday, January 26."]
